# Bump + restart local (full workflow)

When the user asks to **bump** (version/release) **and restart local**, or clearly means the same (e.g. ‚Äúship it‚Äù, ‚Äúrelease bump‚Äù, ‚Äúbump and restart‚Äù, ‚Äúnew build on GitHub‚Äù), do **all** of the following unless they explicitly opt out of one step:

1. **Bump** ‚Äî Update repo `VERSION` and move `CHANGELOG.md` `[Unreleased]` into a dated `[X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` section (per `CHANGELOG.md` ‚ÄúReleasing‚Äù).
2. **Commit** ‚Äî `git add` the release-related changes (typically `VERSION`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and any code/docs in that release), write a clear message (e.g. `release vX.Y.Z` or `chore: release vX.Y.Z ‚Äî ‚Ä¶`).
3. **Push** ‚Äî `git push` to `origin` for the **current branch**. **Do not skip push** unless the user says not to or auth/network fails‚Äîreport errors clearly.
   - If **`master`** is **protected** (push rejected, PR required): push **`chore/release-vX.Y.Z`**, reset local **`master`** to **`origin/master`**, give the **‚ÄúOpen a pull request‚Äù** URL, and **merge** when possible (`gh pr merge` if mergeable and allowed, else tell the user to merge on GitHub).
4. **Installer build on GitHub (required)** ‚Äî After **`vX.Y.Z`** exists on **`origin`** (merge to `master` updates **VERSION** ‚Üí **Tag release** workflow creates the tag; may take **1‚Äì3 minutes**):
   - `git fetch origin --tags`
   - Confirm tag: `git ls-remote origin refs/tags/vX.Y.Z` (or retry fetch after a short wait).
   - Run **GitHub CLI** (use full path if `gh` is not on PATH: **`%ProgramFiles%\GitHub CLI\gh.exe`**):

```powershell
$v = (Get-Content -LiteralPath VERSION -Raw).Trim()
$tag = "v$v"
$gh = Join-Path $env:ProgramFiles "GitHub CLI\gh.exe"
& $gh workflow run build-installer.yml --repo jampat000/Grabby --ref $tag
```

   - Paste the **run URL** from `gh` output (or `gh run list --workflow=build-installer.yml --repo jampat000/Grabby -L 1`) so the user can watch **Build installer** finish and get **`GrabbySetup.exe`** on **Releases**.
   - If **`gh`** is missing or not logged in (`gh auth login`), say so and give the same command for them to run.
   - **Duplicate runs** (Tag release also dispatches the workflow) are OK ‚Äî concurrency groups limit overlap; the important part is **a build always queues**.

5. **Restart local** ‚Äî Restart the dev server (**`scripts/dev-start.ps1`** from repo root). **8766** = dev source vs **8765** = installed service.

Do **not** treat ‚Äúbump / release / new build‚Äù as complete without **push** and **queuing the installer workflow** (step 4), when the user expects an installable build.

## When done ‚Äî tell the user (every time)

After the steps above, **briefly confirm**:

1. **Version** ‚Äî `VERSION` = **X.Y.Z**, `CHANGELOG.md` updated.
2. **GitHub** ‚Äî Branch pushed / PR merged; **Actions ‚Üí Build installer** run started (**link**).
3. **Install** ‚Äî When the run is **green**, **`GrabbySetup.exe`** is under **Releases** for **`vX.Y.Z`** (or **Latest**).
4. **Local** ‚Äî Dev URL (**8766** default) and restart if they use source.

## Full end-to-end (‚Äúnew version + installer + local dev‚Äù)

1. Release branch ‚Üí PR ‚Üí **merge** to **`master`**.
2. **`git fetch origin --tags`** ‚Üí **`gh workflow run build-installer.yml --repo jampat000/Grabby --ref vX.Y.Z`** (after tag exists).
3. **`git pull origin master`** locally.
4. **`scripts/dev-start.ps1`**.

**Run** terminal steps (including **`gh workflow run`**) for the user when possible‚Äîdon‚Äôt only describe them.
